TI  - Assessment of Pendelluft Using Electrical Impedance Tomography in a Patient With 
      Flail Chest.
PG  - e70583
LID - 10.1002/rcr2.70583 [doi]
LID - e70583
AB  - An 80-year-old man with flail chest exhibiting paradoxical chest wall movement 
      required mechanical ventilation for internal fixation. Despite the apparent 
      paradoxical motion resolution, unstable chest wall segments allowed pendelluft to 
      persist. Thus, EIT-guided management of flail chest should focus on stabilising 
      the visible chest wall and achieving homogenised ventilation dynamics.
