TI  - Rare Case of Acute Pulmonary Thromboembolism After Internal Fixation of Multiple 
      Rib Fractures.
PG  - e70899
LID - 10.1002/ccr3.70899 [doi]
LID - e70899
AB  - Acute pulmonary thromboembolism (PTE) after isolated multiple rib fractures is 
      rare; although surgical stabilization of rib fractures (SSRF) is a relatively 
      safe and effective treatment for multiple rib fractures with dislocation, 
      perioperative PTE should be given sufficient attention by clinicians. The 
      standardized prevention of perioperative venous thromboembolism for multiple rib 
      fractures requires further research due to the lack of high-quality clinical 
      evidence support.
