TI  - Blunt chest wall trauma: Rib fractures and associated injuries.
PG  - 25-31
LID - 10.1097/01.JAA.0000885136.91189.83 [doi]
AB  - Blunt injuries to the chest wall, specifically those related to rib fractures, 
      need to be promptly identified and effectively managed to reduce patient 
      morbidity and mortality. Furthermore, judicious use of multimodal pain management 
      and early identification of patients who will benefit from the surgical 
      stabilization of rib fractures are paramount to optimal outcomes.
