VI  - 10
DP  - 2022 Sep
TI  - Rib fracture management: A review of surgical stabilization, regional analgesia, 
      and intercostal nerve cryoablation.
PG  - 100089
LID - 10.1016/j.sipas.2022.100089 [doi]
LID - 100089
AB  - Rib fractures still remain a common problem in blunt thoracic trauma, often 
      resulting significant acute and/or chronic morbidity and mortality. The 
      management of rib fractures has improved over the past two decades, resulting in 
      overall improved patient outcomes. With advances in surgical stabilization of rib 
      fractures (SSRF), improvements in regional analgesia, and the introduction of 
      intercostal nerve cryoablation, patient outcomes from rib fractures have improved 
      significantly over the past several years. This article explores the indications 
      and technique for SSRF as well as discusses additional therapeutic modalities for 
      rib fractures through regional anesthesia and intercostal nerve cryoablation.
