DP  - 2019 Apr
TI  - Surgical management of multiple rib fractures/flail chest.
PG  - 1668-1675
LID - 10.21037/jtd.2019.03.54 [doi]
AB  - Rib fractures in the setting of trauma carries a high morbidity and mortality. 
      Forty-three percent of patients presenting with trauma will have rib fractures. 
      Fifty-five percent of patients, greater than 60 years of age, who die following 
      chest trauma, have isolated rib fractures. Mortality associated with rib 
      fractures starts to increase from the age of 45. Rib fixation is being utilised 
      more for the management of rib fractures. Following the review of literature, we 
      propose a pathway for the management of both simple rib fractures and flail 
      segments. Furthermore, we review the various methods of rib fixation, discussing 
      the advantages and disadvantages of each.
