TI  - Manubriosternal joint dislocation due to blunt force trauma.
PG  - 100187
LID - 10.1016/j.tcr.2019.100187 [doi]
LID - 100187
AB  - A 35-year-old woman was involved in a motor vehicle collision and suffered a 
      manubriosternal joint dislocation with posterior subluxation of the manubrium. 
      She underwent open reduction and internal fixation with sternal plate 
      reconstruction. This report highlights the mechanism and management of these rare 
      traumatic chest wall injuries.
