PMID- 32318653
OWN - NLM
STAT- PubMed-not-MEDLINE
LR  - 20200928
IS  - 2542-6281 (Electronic)
IS  - 2542-6281 (Linking)
VI  - 4
IP  - 1
DP  - 2019
TI  - Vertical Plate for Flail Chest Repair.
PG  - 52-54
LID - 10.4103/jctt.jctt_10_19 [doi]
AB  - Operative treatment of rib fractures in the context of flail chest and 
      respiratory failure is a well-established approach. In-line rib osteosynthesis 
      with plates is the standard treatment sufficient to eliminate flail, achieve 
      sufficient stability, and create chest rigidity to improve the respiratory cycle 
      and maintain reduction. However, bridging large skeletal defects with missing 
      portion of ribs is very challenging, particularly in the absence of suitable 
      anchoring rib fragments. We describe an unusual use of vertical plate rib 
      osteosynthesis in a patient with traumatic flail chest, exacerbated by a prior 
      thoracoplasty and severe osteoporosis.
