TI  - Simultaneous Surgical Treatment of Sternum and Costal Cartilage Fractures.
PG  - e119-e120
LID - S0003-4975(18)31048-8 [pii]
LID - 10.1016/j.athoracsur.2018.06.044 [doi]
AB  - Studies have confirmed that, for severe flail chest or sternal fractures and even 
      multiple rib fractures, surgical treatment can effectively reduce hospital stay 
      and relieve chest wall pain. However, fixation of multiple costal cartilage 
      fractures in such a small area is a challenge if an internal fixator is simply 
      placed directly on the sternum. This case report shares a method of simultaneous 
      fixation of multiple costal cartilage and sternal fractures through a small 
      incision, and it is also appropriate for multiple costal cartilage fractures 
      without sternal fracture.
