TI  - Surgical Stabilization of Rib Fractures in a 6-Year-Old Child After Blunt Trauma.
PG  - e439-e441
LID - S0003-4975(17)31074-3 [pii]
LID - 10.1016/j.athoracsur.2017.07.034 [doi]
AB  - When identified, rib fractures in children are associated with high-energy 
      trauma, nonaccidental trauma, or both. Traditionally, the optimal management of 
      rib fractures in children is supportive care. In this case report, we present a 
      6-year-old boy who underwent surgical rib fixation for multiple displaced and 
      comminuted rib fractures after being stepped on by a horse.
