TI  - Stabilization of Flail Chest and Fractured Sternum by Minimally Invasive Repair 
      of Pectus Excavatum.
PG  - 11-3
LID - 10.1055/s-0035-1563399 [doi]
AB  - We report a 55-year-old male patient with a massive flail chest that required 
      chest stabilization by minimally invasive repair of pectus excavatum (MIRPE) 
      employing a Nuss bar. Surgical stabilization of severe flail chest and fractured 
      sternum with Nuss bar by MIRPE is a safe and useful treatment modality in 
      properly selected patients.
