TI  - An unexpected complication of titanium rib clips.
PG  - 2206-9
LID - S0003-4975(14)00474-3 [pii]
LID - 10.1016/j.athoracsur.2014.02.054 [doi]
AB  - Surgical stabilization of the rib fractures has been successfully performed for 
      the management of pain in multiple rib fractures, fixation of chronically painful 
      nonunion, reduction of overriding ribs, and flail chest cases. Herein we report a 
      patient who was treated with titanium rib clips after a motor vehicle accident 
      leading to pulmonary parenchymal laceration and multiple painful rib fractures. 
      Three of the rib clips were broken 4 months after the operation. The patient 
      underwent the second operation for restabilization of the broken ribs. We review 
      the relevant literature, with particular emphasis on the management of this 
      complication.
