TI  - Rigid plate fixation promotes better bone healing after sternotomy.
PG  - 147-50
LID - S1043-0679(12)00123-2 [pii]
LID - 10.1053/j.semtcvs.2012.08.004 [doi]
AB  - Sternotomy is the most common surgically created osteotomy in surgery. Rigid 
      fixation of osteotomies are important for stability and bony union. This review 
      shows the superiority of rigid plate fixation in achieving better bone healing 
      after sternotomy. It also highlights use of plate fixation for mini-sternotomies 
      and rib fractures.
