TI  - Operative treatment of chest wall injuries: indications, technique, and outcomes.
PG  - 97-110
LID - 10.2106/JBJS.I.00696 [doi]
AB  - Most injuries to the chest wall with residual deformity do not result in 
      long-term respiratory dysfunction unless they are associated with pulmonary 
      contusion. Indications for operative fixation include flail chest, reduction of 
      pain and disability, a chest wall deformity or defect, symptomatic nonunion, 
      thoracotomy for other indications, and open fractures. Operative indications for 
      chest wall injuries are rare.
