TI  - Surgical management of chest wall trauma.
PG  - 475-85
LID - 10.1016/j.thorsurg.2010.07.004 [doi]
AB  - Recent paradigm shift in major trauma profile elevates chest wall injuries among 
      the most important topics of the specialty. Due to mass casualties of terror 
      attacks and asymmetric warfare, civilian and military trauma care challenges 
      thoracic surgery, traumatology, intensive anesthesiology, and related 
      specialties. Contemporary advances of the main issues are systemically presented 
      and discussed, such as soft tissue and bony structure injuries, complex traumas 
      like flail chest, and extensively destroyed chest wall.
