TI  - Reoperative surgical stabilization of a painful nonunited rib fracture using bone 
      grafting and a metal plate.
PG  - 605-6
LID - 10.1097/BOT.0b013e3181a16123 [doi]
AB  - We report a case of a nonunited sixth rib in a patient with multiple rib 
      fractures who underwent internal fixation using a wire and Judet strut 3 times. 
      During the following 3 years, the patient continued to complain of pain and 
      instability. At surgery, a pseudarthrosis between the ends of the sixth rib was 
      excised. A longitudinal gutter crossing the fracture site was fashioned and 
      splinted with an inlay block of cancellous bone grafted from the iliac crest; 
      stabilization was accomplished with a reconstruction plate and screws. The 
      following 2 years of follow-up demonstrated no instability or pain.
