TI  - Novel use of hand fracture fixation plates in the surgical stabilisation of flail 
      chest.
PG  - e51-3
LID - 10.1016/j.bjps.2009.05.012 [doi]
AB  - Plastic surgeons specialize in working closely with other surgical colleagues to 
      help solve clinical problems. In this case, we performed surgical stabilisation 
      of a large flail chest fragment in conjunction with the cardiothoracic surgical 
      team, using the mini-plating set more commonly used for hand fracture fixation. 
      The use of this fixation system for flail chest has not previously been 
      described, but offers advantages over other reported methods, primarily by 
      dispensing with the need for an extensive thoracotomy incision and by providing 
      robust stabilisation without the presence of prominent hardware.
