TI  - Operative stabilization of flail chest using a prosthetic mesh and 
      methylmethacrylate.
PG  - 1064-6
AB  - Surgical stabilization of flail chest is a controversial operation, but recent 
      data has shown that selected patients benefit from it. We describe a simple and 
      practical method of operative stabilization of flail chest using a prosthetic 
      mesh and methylmethacrylate anchored to the ribs and sternum. The 
      methylmethacrylate-mesh complex is inexpensive, can be extracted electively as 
      soon as full thoracic stability is achieved, and can be used to stabilize 
      extended chest wall injuries.
