TI  - [Triple fracture of the superior shoulder suspensory complex].
PG  - 68-72
AB  - The authors present the case of a displaced fracture of the coracoid process 
      associated with a displaced fracture of the acromion, an undisplaced fracture of 
      the clavicule and fractures of the first to fifth ribs. Open reduction of the 
      coracoid process fracture was performed. At the last follow-up, the coracohumeral 
      distance was restored (10 mm), but the acromiohumeral distance in the sagittal 
      place was decreased (5 mm). The authors recommend open reduction of displaced 
      fractures around the rotator cuff to limit the risk of impingement between the 
      cuff and the coracoid process or the acromion.
