VI  - 55
IP  - 5
DP  - 1989 Jan
TI  - [Surgical treatment of the unstable thorax in respiratory insufficiency].
PG  - 711-7
AB  - Sixteen patients with traumatic flail chest underwent surgical stabilization 
      using procedures introduced by Rehbein, Judet and Vecsei. Compared with sixteen 
      patients treated by internal stabilization with intermittent positive pressure 
      respiration, there are some advantages: time of artificial respiration is 
      shortened, early mobilization is possible, nursing is easier, the costs are 
      lower. The procedure is indicated in those patients, in whom long-term artificial 
      respiration is not necessary for other reasons.
