VI  - 21
IP  - 6
DP  - 1989
TI  - Rib fracture healing after osteosynthesis with wire mesh titanium and screws: a 
      histological study in sheep.
PG  - 347-54
AB  - Twenty sheep were placed under general anesthesia and five ribs (6-10) were 
      transected at their lateral angle using a pair of rib shears. The fractures were 
      stabilized by titanium wire mesh plates. After 4, 6, 8, 10 and 12 weeks groups of 
      4 animals were sacrificed and rib samples were prepared for histological 
      examinations. The study showed that the osteosynthesis stabilized the fractures 
      and that the healing is similar to untreated rib fractures. This osteosynthesis 
      method is a good contribution to severe injured chest treatment.
