IS  - 0023-8236 (Linking)
VI  - 367
IP  - 3
DP  - 1986
TI  - [Intrathoracic dislocation of the head of the humerus].
PG  - 197-202
AB  - Intrathoracic displacement of the proximal humerus following axillary luxation is 
      a rare injury; but with ipsilateral serial costal fracture and/or single costal 
      fracture with contused lung it has to be included in the considerations 
      concerning differential diagnosis and the tactics of surgical approach. The 
      primary measures are determined by the extent of pulmonary damage; the further 
      course is marked by aseptic necrosis of the head of the humerus. On the basis of 
      our study case we are describing a typical course, and discussing its problems 
      taking into consideration the individual publications available so far.
