LR  - 20061115
IS  - 0342-7498 (Print)
IS  - 0342-7498 (Linking)
VI  - 33 Suppl 1
DP  - 1979 Apr
TI  - [Surgical aspects during the intensive care of chest trauma (author's transl)].
PG  - 502-6
AB  - A wide range of surgical methods is available in the intensive care of patients 
      with a chest trauma. Discussions with the anaesthetist as to the planning and 
      co-ordination of diagnosis and treatment must take into consideration a great 
      number of factors. The indications for surgery in polytraumatized persons are 
      different from those that apply to single injuries. Table 6 which lists the cause 
      and time of death of 52 persons with multiple injuries provides evidence that 
      during the first 7 days after a severe accident all surgical intervention that is 
      not absolutely necessary should be avoided and attention focused on the problem 
      of adequate ventilation and primary and secondary complications of shock.
