TI  - [Surgical treatment of the flail chest (author's transl)].
PG  - 275-9
AB  - Six patients with traumatic flail chest underwent surgical stabilization using a 
      procedure introduced by Brunner, Hoffmeister and Koncz (2). Compared with 
      internal stabilization by intermittend positive pressure respiration (IPPR), 
      there are some advantages: Time of artificial respiration is shortened, early 
      mobilization is possible, nursing is easier. The procedure is simple to do and is 
      indicated in those patients, in whom longterm artificial respiration is not 
      necessary for other reasons.
