TI  - [Original surgical technic for the treatment of flail chest (author's transl)].
PG  - 293-8
AB  - Solid internal fixation of fractures of the ribs and thorax producing a flail 
      chest is described using a new technic which permits early mobilisation of the 
      patient, immediate spontaneous respiration, abolition of pain, early respiratory 
      physiotherapy, and reduces the danger of respiratory complications due to 
      artificial ventilation, and permenent sequelae due to a secondary deformity of 
      the thoracic cage. Our experience of the method has permitted us to determine its 
      indications and limits.
